The paper deals with lossless variable-length source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on codeword cost, which is related to the compression rate and hence can be considered a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of information-spectrum methods suggests a connection to spectral graph theory and related topics in computer science (cs.DS). The analysis of overflow probability involves probability theory and statistics, which are relevant to machine learning and data science (cs.LG). Finally, the problem of unequal cost function is a general topic that can be applied to various fields, including signal processing and communication systems (cs.SI).
